metadata.name: Breakers #559
metadata.description:
Companion project to Neural Collapse (#15780), for the collectors of my previous efforts.
A study on the repetition and stacking of a simple dynamic structure, this time inside a cylinder.

Everything procedurally generated at runtime.

Interactivity : 
- You can click on each individual breaker to open or close them. The problem is it will toggle others.
- Press and hold the mouse button to slightly move the viewpoint. The previous interaction not being disabled while doing that, you get some switching all over the place as a bonus bug/feature.

- Press "a" to increase quality of the antialiasing (3 levels), at the cost of performances. If you don't like jaggies and your machine can take it.
- Export a PNG capture at various resolutions by pressing the number keys 1 to 9 (top row or numpad, and only in live mode, after pressing "open"). Resolutions ranges from 720 to 7680 pixels. I recommend starting with "4".

GPU recommended. Best performances on Chrome in general.

metadata.name: Tezumie 1-1 #525
metadata.description:
Tezumie have found themselves in Dimension 1-1, the perfect place for an adventure!

-WARNING-
They may seem to be a cute companion to hang out in your browser, but DO NOT leave them there for extended periods.  

Side effects may include: Missing items in your household, odd behavior in pets, a strange odor, prolonged nightmares, restless leg syndrome, hearing colors, missing teeth, uncontrollable urges, existential crisis, temporary blindness, and a strong appetite for non-edible objects.

Special Thanks to the following creators for permitting traits based on their art/style/projects;

AgataPoison, Craigers , griza, iRyanBell, Jim the Bim, KilledByAPixel, Liam Egan, Littlesilver, lucky26, MarkKnol, ozzie, PersonChen, punevyr, and the creators of MIME x MIME.

-CONTROLS-
(W)-Toggle weather
(F)-Toggle frame 
(C)-Toggle cursor
(P)–Pause
(A)-Shrink
(D)-Grow
(SHIFT + S)-Save image
(SHIFT + G)-Save 4 frames that you can use to make a GIF, see “sketch.js” for further instructions.

Made in p5js.

metadata.name: MONOLITH #70
metadata.description:
Very limited facts are known about these strange monolithic structures. Black, rectilinear, similar to obsidian stone but made of strange materials. According to legend, an ancient civilization of high intelligence, called the Explorers of Latent Space, distributed hundreds of monoliths throughout time and space in order to study the behavior of species in the infinite Universe.

Some say that it is the divine intelligence of God. Others say that, in spite of their objectual and material condition, the monoliths possess their own consciousness and an intelligence beyond the natural and artificial. Their purpose or objective, to this day, remains a mystery.

_-_-_-_-_-_-_-_

metadata.name: CrossWorlds #137
metadata.description:
In 2057 an error occurred in the particle accelerator machine causing a diversion in space-time that leads to duplication of our world. Scientists discovered that they can travel to these "CrossWorlds" with wormholes plagued by singularities occurring at weakened points of the fabric between worlds. In time, some worlds became hostile to each other, tried to plunder their natural resources, and take over civilizations but other worlds learned how to co-exist peacefully...
------------------
Animation_
Press R: Rotates the world 180°
Idle: Default animation cycles from corner to corner
Mouse: Cursor-dependent animation
MobileDevice: Controls the animation with the orientation of the device. (Android only)
------------------
Live-view_
Resolution: Add "&res=" end of your url with a resolution multiplier. (0.5-6)
Press S: Saves the current scene (Default 1600x1600 px).
Press L: Zip file containing all drawing layers separately as PNG.
Press D: Zip file containing all drawing layers separately as SVG.
------------------
Created with p5js.

metadata.name: Sugar & Splice #316
metadata.description:
'Sugar & Splice'

Vibrant somethings, full of flavor, dancing within conjoined boundaries.

Controls:
s: Saves an image of the canvas with the current settings
1-6: Scales the canvas size, from 1 (default, 2048px x 2792px) to 6 (12288px x  16752px)
g: Toggles grain texture
t: Toggles background transparency
f: Toggles fit to screen (layout and other factors will change based on the new size, but overall style, colors, etc will remain the same)
p: Shortcut for large print settings: disables the grain texture and scales the canvas to the largest setting
b: Toggles b-side

metadata.name: Aeoflu #57
metadata.description:
This broadcast is transmitted to the brains of the humanoid race from the planet Xiurq during hyperspace travel. The algorithm is specifically designed to preserve the cognitive functions of the species during "slow time" and overload. The use of the algorithm by other races has not been studied. Prohibited for use outside specially certified laboratories by intergalactic convention 30292-HD-92 

The idea of this project is infinite motion, but it can be stopped (“space”) and save static image ("s" button)

There are three modes. They are switched by click. Each switch changes the input parameters, so there are quite a few options

!!!Flashing lights seizure warning!!!
